.TH PLERRY 3plplot  "June, 2019" "" "PLplot API"
.SH NAME
\fBplerry\fP - Draw error bars in the y direction
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBplerry\fP(\fIn\fP, \fIx\fP, \fIymin\fP, \fIymax\fP)
.SH DESCRIPTION

.P
Draws a set of \fIn\fP error bars in the y direction, the i'th error bar extending from \fIymin\fP[i] to \fIymax\fP[i] at x coordinate \fIx\fP[i].  The terminals of the error bars are of length equal to the minor tick length (settable using \fBplsmin\fP(3plplot)).
.P
Redacted form: General: \fBplerry(x, ymin, ymax)\fP

.P
This function is used in example 29.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
\fIn\fP (\fBPLINT\fP(3plplot), input)
Number of error bars to draw.
.TP
\fIx\fP (\fBPLFLT_VECTOR\fP(3plplot), input)
A vector containing the x coordinates of the error bars.
.TP
\fIymin\fP (\fBPLFLT_VECTOR\fP(3plplot), input)
A vector containing the y coordinates of the lower endpoints of the error bars.
.TP
\fIymax\fP (\fBPLFLT_VECTOR\fP(3plplot), input)
A vector containing the y coordinates of the upper endpoints of the error bars.

